iant, caustic, and imperious Bentley revealed to polite readers the doings of professional scholars and induced them to pay attention to classical study. At the same time, Europe's most famous classical scholar adapted his own publications to the deficiencies of non-expert readers. Abandoning the church-oriented historical study of his peers, he worked on texts that interested a wider public, with spectacular and—in the case of his interventionist edition of Paradise Lost—sometimes lamentable results. If the union of worlds Bentley craved was not to be achieved in his lifetime, his provocations show that professional humanism left a deep imprint on the literary world of England's Enlightenment.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aCivilization, ClassicalxStudy and teachingxHistoryxEngland. 0aCivilization, ClassicalxStudy and teachingzEnglandxHistory. 0aClassicistsxGreat Britain. 0aClassicistszGreat Britain. 0aCriticism, TextualxHistoryxVerenigd Koninkrijk van Groot-Brittannië en Noord-Ierland. 0aCriticism, TextualxHistory. 0aLearning and scholarshipxHistoryxEngland. 0aLearning and scholarshipzEnglandxHistory. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Literary.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2011z9783110261189oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LANGUAGES TITLES 2011z978311026123308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK UND LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2011z9783110261240oZDB-23-DGA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013 (Canada)z978311075606708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHarvard University Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831104422050 cprintz978067405871240uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/harv